{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make responsible pet ownership teaching mandatory in schools",
        "additional_details": "We believe bridging the gap between education and understanding responsible pet ownership is the only way we can improve on the current crisis.\r\n \r\nBritain is a country which prides itself as a nation of animal lovers. However, there is no mandatory education on responsible pet ownership despite 57% of UK households owning a pet.\r\n \r\nAs we\u2019ve entered into the post-lockdown period, rescue centres are inundated with abandoned or stray animals.\r\n \r\nWe believe the root of the current pet overpopulation problem can be traced back to a lack of accurate and up to date understanding relating to responsible pet ownership, including neutering and the benefits it can provide.\r\n",
        "background": "As someone that has worked in both the veterinary and animal rescue industry I\u2019ve seen first-hand the nationwide gap in education relating to pet care.",
